{"questionId":"15746","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{1}{3}{x^3} + \\frac{1}{2}{x^2} + kx + 5\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>k</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;has a local maximum and a local minimum. The local maximum is at <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x =&nbsp; - 3\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the interval where the gradient of the graph of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> is negative.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - 3 < x < 2\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;(A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em> for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x&nbsp;> - 3\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span> , <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong> for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x < 2\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>. Follow through for their \"2\" in part (b). It is possible to award <em><strong>(A0)(A1)</strong></em>. For <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - 3 <&nbsp;y < 2\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span> award <em><strong>(A1)(A0)</strong></em>. Accept equivalent notation such as (−3, 2). Award <em><strong>(A0)</strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong> for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - 3 \\leqslant x \\leqslant 2\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15746","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ1.T_6c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the interval where the gradient of the graph of f ( x ) is negative.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.1—Introduction of differential calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.2—Increasing and decreasing functions","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.4—Tangents and normal","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}